&gt; On Dec 21, 2009, at 3:11 PM, Roger Gonzalez wrote:
&gt;
&gt; &gt; Any given resource may have multiple representations that have exactly
&gt; &gt; the same media type; for example, an image resource may have an
&gt; &gt; image/png representing the full content as well as an image/png
&gt; &gt; representing a thumbnail. Content negotiation based only on media type
&gt; &gt; isn&#39;t sufficient.
&gt;
&gt; Exactly. No silver bullets here. Your example highlights why treating a
